(- signing_message_hex_digest\(tx\) builds a deterministic string from version, lock_time, sorted) Tj
T*
(inputs/outputs, metadata, and tx_id, then sha3_384\(...\).hexdigest\(\).lower\(\).) Tj
T*
(- Excludes witness/signature/pubkey; SegWit-style.) Tj
T*
(- Signing path:) Tj
T*
(- Src/Main/send.py builds the tx, then calls KeyManager.sign_transaction.) Tj
T*
(- KeyManager.sign_transaction normalizes the signing message to hex \(detects 48-byte or 96-char) Tj
T*
(SHA3-384 digests\), then calls FalconCLI.sign on that hex string.) Tj
T*
(- Signature is stored once at tx.signature \(witness\); inputs do not carry the full sig.) Tj
T*
(- On wire, witness signature/pubkey are canonical base64; verifier decodes them back to) Tj
T*
(bytes/hex before Falcon checks.) Tj
T*
(- Verification path:) Tj
T*
(- Src/Transactions/txvalidation.py::_validate_signature strips witness \(SegWit.strip_witness\),) Tj
T*
(recomputes signing_message_hex_digest, and calls KeyManager.verify_transaction.) Tj
T*
(- KeyManager.verify_transaction prefers 96-char SHA3-384 hex inputs, normalizes signature, and) Tj
T*
(drives FalconCLI.verify \(CLI-first, optional FFI\) with multiple argument orders.) Tj
T*
(- Failure rejects the transaction before fee/UTXO checks.) Tj
T*
(- Merkle/txid use:) Tj
T*
(- Src/SigWit/sigwit.py and Src/Utility/hash.py::merkle_root_from_hex use SHA3-384 for merkle) Tj
T*
(parents; txids are assumed to be SHA3-384 hex.) Tj
T*
() Tj
