(Audit notes / risks) Tj
T*
(- HPK derivation is deterministic SHA3-384; ensure all key import paths use the same) Tj
T*
(normalization \(they do via key_manager.py and change_default_key.py import flow\). Mixing) Tj
T*
(uppercase/lowercase hex could break checksum/user display if altered before hashing; current) Tj
T*
(code lowercases.) Tj
T*
(- Base56 checksum uses SHA3-256 \(not 384\). Address integrity depends on this checksum plus) Tj
T*
(network prefix; no Bech32-style polymod?keep checksum verification intact.) Tj
T*
(- Signature acceptance allows 1024-hex signatures as well as 2048-hex \(in) Tj
T*
(KeyManager.verify_transaction\); tighten to 2048 if only Falcon-512 is intended.) Tj
T*
(- Signing temp files \(for Falcon CLI\) contain private key components; they are overwritten and) Tj
T*
(deleted best-effort. Use secured temp dirs or in-memory pipes if higher assurance is needed.) Tj
T*
(- On required networks, startup fails if Falcon pinning is required and no expected digest is) Tj
T*
(configured for the active consensus version.) Tj
T*
(- Witness exclusion: txid/signing digest intentionally exclude tx.signature; ensure downstream) Tj
T*
(tools don?t accidentally rehash with witness included.) Tj
T*
() Tj
